==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ripe
<hw>Ripe</hw> <pr>(r⟦imac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Riper</adjf>
<pr>(r⟦imac⟧p"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Ripest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>r⟦imac⟧pe</ets>; akin to
OS. <ets>r⟦imac⟧pi</ets>, D. <ets>rijp</ets>, G. <ets>rief</ets>, OHG.
<ets>r⟦imac⟧ft</ets>; cf. AS. <ets>r⟦imac⟧p</ets> harvest,
<ets>r⟦imac⟧pan</ets> to reap. Cf. <er>Reap</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Ready for reaping or gathering; having attained perfection; mature;
-- said of fruits, seeds, etc.; <as>as, <ex>ripe</ex>
grain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So mayst thou live, till, like <qex>ripe</qex> fruit, thou
drop⟦br⟧
Into thy mother's lap.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Advanced to the state of fitness for use; mellow;
<as>as, <ex>ripe</ex> cheese; <ex>ripe</ex> wine.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having attained its full development; mature;
perfected; consummate.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Ripe</xex> courage.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was a scholar, and a <qex>ripe</qex> and good one.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Maturated or suppurated; ready to discharge; -- said
of sores, tumors, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Ready for action or effect; prepared.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While things were just <qex>ripe</qex> for a war.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am not <qex>ripe</qex> to pass sentence on the gravest public
bodies.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Like ripened fruit in ruddiness and
plumpness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those happy smilets,⟦br⟧
That played on her <qex>ripe</qex> lip.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Intoxicated.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Reeling <xex>ripe</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Mature; complete; finished. See
<er>Mature</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ripe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Ripe
<hw>Ripe</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>r⟦imac⟧pian</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To ripen; to grow ripe.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ripe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Ripe
<hw>Ripe</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To mature; to ripen.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ripely</ent>⟦br⟧
